<paragraph blockId="0.[1621,2722,613,707]" box="[1621,2722,613,701]" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">(SHEATH-TAILED BATS)</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="349">• Small- to medium-sized insectivorous bats with tail protruding above uropatagium radio-metacarpal sacs and gular sac often prominent in males.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1640,1909,946,988]" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">• 3-5-17 cm.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="349">
• 
<emphasis box="[1684,1940,1266,1308]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">Afrotropical</emphasis>
, Indo-Malayan, 
<emphasis box="[2278,2533,1266,1308]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">Australasian</emphasis>
, Neotropical, and Holarctic (marginally) Regions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1639,2785,1371,1413]" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">• Closed and open forests to savannas and semi-deserts.</paragraph>
<paragraph box="[1639,2298,1425,1467]" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">
• 14 genera, 54 
<emphasis box="[1976,2122,1425,1467]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">species</emphasis>
, 94 taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="349">
• 1 
<emphasis box="[1744,1886,1477,1519]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="349">species</emphasis>
Critically Endangered, 2 Endangered, 3 Vulnerable; none Extinct since 1600.
</paragraph>
